data.meta_description: Princess Maria Pia of Bourbon-Two Sicilies (1849â€“1882). She was a daughter of  King Ferdinand II of the Two Sicilies and Archduchess Maria Theresa of Austria. She married Roberto I duke of Parma.  Maria Pia had twelve children in thirteen years.  Three of her children died in childhood, nine reach adulthood, but six of them were mentally disabled. Only three of her children: two daughters and one son were healthy.
